WEBVTT

00:00.896 --> 00:03.063
Welcome to Barbados.

00:03.565 --> 00:05.832
All visitors please proceed...

00:05.834 --> 00:09.736
Ok, come on.
It's not much farther.

00:09.738 --> 00:11.237
How about a piggyback ride?

00:11.239 --> 00:12.739
I will fall over.

00:12.741 --> 00:15.675
But it's just so heavy.

00:15.677 --> 00:17.410
Yeah, right. Ok.

00:17.412 --> 00:18.745
Thanks, Mom.

00:19.580 --> 00:20.847
There's no Wifi.

00:20.849 --> 00:22.448
There'll be some
at the hotel.

00:22.450 --> 00:24.684
I told grandma I'd text her
when we landed.

00:24.686 --> 00:27.020
Yes, but this trip isn't about texting,
it's about unplugging.

00:27.022 --> 00:29.556
So you're not gonna be
on your phone at all?

00:29.558 --> 00:31.024
Please don't do this.
I have such a pounding headache.

00:31.026 --> 00:34.827
Your allergies,
they're the worst.

00:38.033 --> 00:39.766
All right, check it out,
buddy.

00:39.768 --> 00:42.669
7 pools, 9 waterslides,

00:42.671 --> 00:44.804
a mile-long lazy river,

00:44.806 --> 00:47.440
and if you dare,
there's roaring rapids.

00:47.442 --> 00:49.075
Don't forget about
the dolphins.

00:49.077 --> 00:50.577
Oh, yeah. Did you make
that reservation?

00:50.579 --> 00:52.345
10 a.m. tomorrow.

00:52.347 --> 00:53.680
Can we surf on them?

00:53.682 --> 00:54.647
Yeah.

00:54.649 --> 00:56.049
No.
No.

00:56.051 --> 00:57.584
Ah, here we go.
Yeah, yeah, that's...

00:57.586 --> 00:58.818
Yay.

01:05.159 --> 01:06.659
Oh, no.

01:08.762 --> 01:11.297
Website said the last
shuttle left at 10:00.

01:11.299 --> 01:12.765
I lost track of time.

01:12.767 --> 01:14.167
Want to take a taxi?

01:14.169 --> 01:15.501
No, we have too much stuff.

01:15.503 --> 01:17.303
We'll never fit.
We'd have to take two cabs.

01:17.305 --> 01:18.838
It's late.
I don't want to split up.

01:18.840 --> 01:20.640
Ok. Ok.

01:20.642 --> 01:22.408
Ok.
Oh, hang on.

01:23.444 --> 01:26.379
Hey, how much to take us
to the Grand Royal?

01:26.381 --> 01:28.615
I hope this guy
can take us.

01:28.617 --> 01:29.582
Thanks.

01:29.584 --> 01:32.685
This guy, 45 minutes,
45 bucks.

01:32.687 --> 01:34.787
Great.

01:36.757 --> 01:38.591
Hop in, kids.

01:45.566 --> 01:48.067
There's complimentary
water in the cooler.

01:48.069 --> 01:49.669
Oh, thanks.

01:49.671 --> 01:52.005
Hey, guys,
get these down, ok?

01:52.007 --> 01:53.506
Mm-hmm?
Honey?

01:53.508 --> 01:56.409
This is the best way to avoid any bugs
you got on the plane.

01:56.411 --> 01:57.577
Mm.

01:58.746 --> 02:02.515
Driver: So where you guys from?

02:02.517 --> 02:04.350
Uh, D.C. area.

02:04.352 --> 02:05.551
You ever been?

02:05.553 --> 02:06.753
When I was a kid, yeah.

02:06.755 --> 02:08.288
Loved the museums.

02:08.289 --> 02:10.490
We got some good places
around here you should check out.

02:10.491 --> 02:12.659
Your kids into history?

02:12.661 --> 02:14.027
Sure.

02:14.029 --> 02:16.062
I'll make you a list.

02:16.064 --> 02:17.497
Thanks, that'd be great.

02:21.469 --> 02:24.370
Hey, I think Al's upset
we didn't get her that plan.

02:24.372 --> 02:26.839
Can we fix that tomorrow?

02:26.841 --> 02:30.043
Greg.

02:30.045 --> 02:31.844
Greg.

02:31.846 --> 02:32.879
Greg.

02:32.881 --> 02:34.047
Everything ok?

02:34.049 --> 02:37.016
Yeah. It's a gift.
He can fall asleep anywhere.

02:39.386 --> 02:42.522
Come on, you guys. Hello!

02:42.524 --> 02:44.657
This isn't funny. Wake up.

02:51.498 --> 02:53.599
Greg?

02:53.601 --> 02:54.867
Greg!

02:54.869 --> 02:56.869
Greg!

02:56.871 --> 02:59.872
Ok, something's wrong.
You need to pull over.

03:01.775 --> 03:03.443
Where are you going?!

03:03.445 --> 03:06.679
Where are you going?!

03:08.000 --> 03:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:34.242 --> 03:37.543
The Sullivan family disappeared
in Barbados 8 hours ago.

03:37.545 --> 03:39.445
From the airport?

03:39.447 --> 03:41.147
How old
are the children?

03:41.149 --> 03:42.548
10 and 14.

03:42.550 --> 03:44.884
Here we go again.

03:44.886 --> 03:46.919
Barbados? Americans
on foreign soil

03:46.921 --> 03:48.588
is Jack Garrett's territory.

03:48.590 --> 03:50.323
Cruz says
there's more to it.

03:50.325 --> 03:51.591
How you been, Jack?

03:51.593 --> 03:54.927
Busy. I wish this
was under better circumstances.

03:54.929 --> 03:57.096
Want to fill us in?

03:58.065 --> 03:59.632
All right,

03:59.634 --> 04:02.101
one last thing.

04:02.103 --> 04:04.470
We know that you're all
at the top of your class,

04:04.472 --> 04:07.807
but any ideas on why I
chose you for this rotation?

04:07.809 --> 04:09.475
Our knowledge
of international law?

04:09.477 --> 04:11.444
Well, that certainly helps.

04:11.446 --> 04:14.647
But your essays revealed
moments that forever changed

04:14.649 --> 04:16.182
the way you look
at the world.

04:16.184 --> 04:18.885
It's your passion for justice.
That's why you're here.

04:18.887 --> 04:20.420
That's what you need
to hold on to.

04:20.422 --> 04:22.188
All right, send me
your thoughts

04:22.190 --> 04:24.957
on the anti-kidnapping initiative
and we will discuss next time.

04:24.959 --> 04:25.959
Thanks, Agent Lambert.

04:25.960 --> 04:27.360
It's Lily.

04:28.996 --> 04:30.830
Jack's on his way.
Wants to debrief in five.

04:30.832 --> 04:31.964
Where's the case?

04:31.966 --> 04:34.167
Barbados.
Family's been kidnapped.

04:34.169 --> 04:35.601
Ok, I need the legal
statutes.

04:35.603 --> 04:36.869
You are the best.

04:36.871 --> 04:38.304
Ambassador's on line 2.

04:38.306 --> 04:41.774
Oh, and see if the Caribbean court
has any revisions.

04:41.776 --> 04:43.042
Ambassador.

04:43.044 --> 04:44.177
Yes, we just heard.

04:45.313 --> 04:46.979
Absolutely.

04:46.981 --> 04:48.114
Matt, hold on.

04:48.116 --> 04:50.616
We'll call you from
the tarmac with our ETA.

04:50.618 --> 04:52.318
See you soon.

04:52.320 --> 04:53.820
How far away are you?

04:53.822 --> 04:55.188
I just left the house.

04:55.190 --> 04:56.556
Matt is 20 minutes away.

04:56.558 --> 04:57.557
Well, tell him he's driving.

04:57.559 --> 04:58.559
Did you hear that?

04:58.560 --> 04:59.792
Yeah. Copy that.

05:00.594 --> 05:02.628
Cruz briefed
Hotch and Rossi.

05:02.630 --> 05:05.164
Is he gathering
the rest of the BAU?

05:05.166 --> 05:07.467
As we speak. Everything
ready in Barbados?

05:07.469 --> 05:09.168
It's coordinated
with the ambassador.

05:09.170 --> 05:10.303
Great.

05:10.305 --> 05:11.971
Our unsub's eluded
both domestic

05:11.973 --> 05:13.439
and international
teams,

05:13.441 --> 05:15.942
and we're not about
to let him get away with it again.

05:15.944 --> 05:17.376
As you all remember,

05:17.378 --> 05:20.112
last April the Isaacs family
was killed in Florida,

05:20.114 --> 05:22.648
and the Everetts were killed in Aruba
the year before that.

05:22.650 --> 05:24.984
Both families were found
24 hours after they were taken.

05:24.986 --> 05:26.486
Each family member
had been strangled

05:26.488 --> 05:28.020
and their bodies were dumped
in a remote area.

05:28.022 --> 05:29.055
The trails went cold.

05:29.057 --> 05:30.490
All signs pointed
to the Everetts

05:30.492 --> 05:31.691
being his first victims.

05:31.693 --> 05:34.527
Because of the hands-on,
intimate nature of the kills,

05:34.529 --> 05:36.128
we thought
it was personal.

05:36.130 --> 05:38.564
And we built on that theory
with the Isaacs in Florida, but to no avail.

05:38.566 --> 05:40.299
Now that he's moved
internationally again,

05:40.301 --> 05:42.201
it's time to rethink
the motive.

05:42.203 --> 05:44.937
It's clear he gets off
on hunting American families

05:44.939 --> 05:46.339
when they're on vacation.

05:46.341 --> 05:50.476
Just over 8 hours ago he abducted
the Sullivans from Barbados.

05:50.478 --> 05:52.011
It feels like he's
establishing a clear pattern.

05:52.013 --> 05:53.679
He started overseas,
came back to the states,

05:53.681 --> 05:55.147
and now he's gone
to another country again.

05:55.149 --> 05:57.183
The month of April
has some sort of significance to him.

05:57.185 --> 05:59.218
Maybe it's easy
hunting season.

05:59.220 --> 06:02.054
All the kills were during
spring break vacations.

06:02.056 --> 06:04.123
It takes guts and skill
to snatch a whole family,

06:04.125 --> 06:05.491
but you wouldn't know it
by watching him.

06:05.493 --> 06:07.927
Rossi: The higher the risk,
the lower his heart rate.

06:07.929 --> 06:09.295
A true sociopath.

06:09.297 --> 06:11.364
And the family's too tired
from a long day of travel

06:11.366 --> 06:12.465
to see the ruse.

06:12.467 --> 06:13.900
And the unsub's probably
too charismatic

06:13.902 --> 06:15.701
to set off any
instinctual alarms.

06:15.703 --> 06:19.272
Cruz: I need both domestic and international
teams working together on this.

06:19.274 --> 06:20.640
If our unsub
sticks to his pattern,

06:20.642 --> 06:22.174
he'll kill the Sullivans
by sunrise.

06:22.176 --> 06:24.810
Kate, you and Reid go to the
Sullivans' house in Fairfax county.

06:24.812 --> 06:27.647
Look for links between
them and the other victims.

06:27.649 --> 06:29.649
We need to establish whether
he's stalking them at their homes

06:29.651 --> 06:30.983
before
they take their trips.

06:30.985 --> 06:33.185
The rest of us
will head to Barbados.

06:34.488 --> 06:36.322
Sir, we don't have
a lot of time.

06:36.324 --> 06:38.324
Please tell me Monty's
on this with us.

06:38.326 --> 06:42.161
Yes, he's on his way.
Agent Simmons will be with us.

06:42.163 --> 06:44.263
So, our jet or yours?

06:44.265 --> 06:46.332
We'll flip for it.

